le Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":20,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":45,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":58,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Staverton was born in 1270, in Bray, Berkshire, England, his father, Staverton, was 21 and his mother, Mrs Staverton, was 21. He married Mrs Robert Staverton in 1295, in Bray, Berkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1332, in his hometown, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1270–1332":"1270–1332","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1310–1360":"1310–1360","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1315":"1315","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","London, , Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Bray, Berkshire, England":"Bray, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1270–1332":"1270–1332","1275–Female":"1275–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1310–1360":"1310–1360","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1315":"